<subSubSection box="[545,1043,1575,1601]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="3.[545,1043,1575,1601]" box="[545,1043,1575,1601]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Ehrenberg, 1838" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1838" box="[674,1043,1575,1601]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Nodosariinae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[674,840,1575,1601]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Nodosariinae</emphasis>
Ehrenberg, 1838
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,310,1640,1666]" box="[189,310,1640,1666]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1640,1666]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1640,1666]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[186,1399,1687,1889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The diagnostic characters of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1838" box="[636,792,1687,1713]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariinae" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="family">Nodosariinae</taxonomicName>
are a uniserial chamber arrangement and a rectilinear to slightly arcuate test in the megalospheric generation, with a terminal aperture made of radiate slits or grooves around the margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Hayward B. W. &amp; Kawagata S. &amp; Sabaa A. &amp; Grenfell H. &amp; Van Kerckhoven L. &amp; Johnson K. &amp; Thomas E." box="[567,823,1757,1783]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="408" refId="ref63648" refString="Hayward B. W., Kawagata S., Sabaa A., Grenfell H., Van Kerckhoven L., Johnson K. &amp; Thomas E. 2012. The last global extinction (Mid-Pleistocene) of deep-sea benthic foraminifera (Chrysalogoniidae, Ellipsoidinidae, Glandulonodosariidae, Plectofrondiculariidae, Pleursostomellidae, Stilostomellidae), their Late Cretaceous-Cenozoic history and taxonomy. Cushman Foundation for Foraminiferal Research Special Publication 43: 408." type="journal article" year="2012">
Hayward 
<emphasis box="[687,749,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). The few and rarely encountered specimens of the microspheric generation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Parr, 1950" authorityName="Parr" authorityYear="1950" box="[568,951,1792,1819]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Dentalina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<emphasis box="[568,815,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dentalina antarctica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Parr W. J." box="[825,951,1792,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="232 - 392" refId="ref65091" refString="Parr W. J. 1950. Foraminifera. B. A. N. Z. Antarctic Research Expedition, 1929 - 1931, Reports, Adelaide, Series B (Zoology, Botany) 5 (6): 232 - 392." type="journal article" year="1950">Parr, 1950</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="d'Orbigny, 1846" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1846" box="[967,1393,1792,1818]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Dentalina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[967,1184,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dentalina elegans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="d'Orbigny A. D." box="[1194,1393,1792,1818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref64879" refString="d'Orbigny A. D. 1846. Die fossilen Foraminiferen des tertiaren Beckens von Wien. Foraminiferes fossiles du bassin tertiaire de Vienne. Guide et Comp, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 145432" type="book" year="1846">d’Orbigny, 1846</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[189,613,1827,1854]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Dentalina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="obliqua">
<emphasis box="[189,408,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dentalina obliqua</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus C. von" box="[428,605,1827,1854]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref64115" refString="Linnaeus C. von 1758. Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tenth Edition. G. Engelman, Lipsiae. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus,1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Neugeboren, 1856" authorityName="Neugeboren" authorityYear="1856" box="[687,1140,1827,1854]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Nodosaria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="incerta">
<emphasis box="[687,906,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Nodosaria incerta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Neugeboren J. L." box="[918,1140,1827,1854]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="65 - 108" refId="ref64648" refString="Neugeboren J. L. 1856. Die Foraminiferen aus der Ordnung der Stichostegier von Ober-Lapugy in Siebenburgen. Denkschriften der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch- Naturwissenschaftliche Classe 12: 65 - 108." type="journal article" year="1856">Neugeboren, 1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have rudiments of a planispiral arrangement of the very first initial chambers.
</paragraph>
